  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight into discovered failures by characterizing their properties and relating them to internal model signals (neuron coverage) and input-sample size, but it does not trace failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., dataset bias, spurious features, corrupted training data, or overfitting) nor analyze failure patterns at the class- or feature-level. Specifically, the authors define and use local and global neuron-coverage measures as the fitness guiding generation, report quantitative correlations between increased neuron coverage / larger initial sample size and the number of erroneous or difference-inducing inputs, and discuss how coverage-guided search finds corner cases. However, they do not analyze the misclassified inputs to explain why the model fails (no linkage of failures to training data issues, spurious features, or internal activation pattern analyses beyond coverage counts).",
